  "excerpt": "This tutorial shows how to automate multiple devices on the same network by using AskUI.",
  "content": "<p id=\">This tutorial shows how to automate multiple devices on the same network by using AskUI. After following this tutorial, you will be able to automate more than one device across different platforms, whether Linux, macOS, Windows or Android, with a single setup with askui library.</p><p id=\">In fact, there are many automation tools in the wild that you can use for testing and automating different devices, although most of them require different configurations and different code for different platforms. By using AskUI library, an automation tool that operates on the OS level, you can use the same code for any application running on different devices even without much change. And this makes AskUI a powerful Cross-platform automation tool.</p><p id=\">Let's have a look at AskUI and see how we can accomplish a Cross-platform/-device automation testüî•</p><p id=\">üìå <em id=\">The following tutorial assumes that you have already installed and set up the AskUI on your local device. See the Getting started for more details:</em></p><ul id=\"><li id=\"><a href=\"https://docs.askui.com/docs/general/Getting%20Started/getting-started\" target=\"_blank\" id=\"><em id=\">Windows</em></a></li><li id=\"><a href=\"https://docs.askui.com/docs/general/Getting%20Started/Installing%20AskUI/getting-started-macos\" id=\">macOS</a></li><li id=\"><a href=\"https://docs.askui.com/docs/general/Getting%20Started/Installing%20AskUI/getting-started-linux\" id=\">Linux</a></li></ul><p id=\">‚Äç</p><figure id=\" class=\"w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-fullwidth\" style=\"max-width:1280px\" data-rt-type=\"image\" data-rt-align=\"fullwidth\" data-rt-max-width=\"1280px\"><div id=\"><img src=\"https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6630f90ff7431b0c5b1bb0e7/6634d1b5517c296559afd675_63b8b20552791ad16c7f8c72_askui-multi-device.png\" loading=\"lazy\" id=\" width=\"auto\" height=\"auto\" alt=\"></div></figure><h2 id=\">1. Start the AskUI Controller for Each Device</h2><h